Chile’s Vapores Rises After Announcing New Share Price

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-25T20:43:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/chile-s-vapores-surges-after-announcing-new-share-price.html
Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA,
 Latin America ’s largest container shipping company, gained the
most in seven weeks in Santiago trading after announcing the
price at which it plans to sell new shares to fund operations.  Vapores rose 3.8 percent to 320.59 pesos at 4 p.m. New York
time, the steepest increase since April 6. Chile’s benchmark
IPSA index rose 0.2 percent to 4,800.82.  The company plans to sell 835 million new shares at 285
pesos each as part of a capital increase approved April 8,
according to a statement sent by the company to the Santiago
stock exchange. The share package is valued at $505 million at
today’s exchange rate.  Current investors will be allowed to buy approximately 0.41
new shares for every share they own by tomorrow, May 26, the
statement said.  “People are seizing the share today to be able to
participate in the capital increase,” Matias Repetto, head of
equity trading at Celfin Capital SA, said today in a phone
interview from Santiago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
